Dear Renato,

It's good to hear that the original error disappeared. Regarding the new 
error, I have no idea, maybe some members of the mailing list are 
familiar with this packages/function and can help you.
In the meantime, you might want to try calling traceback() right after 
the error. It may help you figure out the origin of this error. Also you 
can check the source code of smmcrit() 
(https://rdrr.io/cran/WRS2/src/R/smmcrit.R) and mcp2atm() 
(https://rdrr.io/rforge/WRS2/src/R/mcp2atm.R) to understand the 
not-too-informative error message.

Have a nice weekend,
